bug.short_desc: Scrollbar rendered in wrong place, divides window
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: The scrollbar for scrolling up and down in a buffer is drawn over the top of the right-hand window if I split the frame into two windows and then make the right-hand window larger.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): emacs-25.1-0.3.rc2.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. emacs -Q 2. C-x 3 3. Click and drag left at the intersection of the middle border and the modeline or press C-x { (either will work) to make the right-hand window larger at the expense of the left-hand window.
Actual results: Scrollbar stays at same number of characters from border line, so it divides the right-hand window in two and occludes the view of the right-hand window.
Expected results: Scrollbar should either stay where it is, or overlap the middle border.
Additional info: I am running KDE.
Could you please attach a screenshot? I'm seeing some artifacts as well, but I'm not sure if they are the same or not.
Created attachment 1201998 Screenshot of emacs with misplaced scrollbar

Created attachment 1202335 screenshot2
On my system, I can't reproduce what you are seeing. I can only see a badly drawn fringe on the right (see screenshot).
Any chance you could try another desktop environment, like Gnome or XFCE?
You can also try a new update with the stable release: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-c834d33700
It's working now after updating emacs.
